One big idea that our team was thinking about is ways to prevent the corral from being stuck in the robot. You can replace polycarbonate shielding with 3D printed shielding as a less expensive alternative and it can form more complex shapes. If extra resources are available to you then you have the possibility to create a nice testing bench for programming different sections of the robot while they are separate.

These aren’t cool, but they’re useful.

  1. Simple mounts
  2. Spacers
  3. Or just parts in general

Being able to 3D print in general is awesome and it opens up a whole nother door of things you can make.

Although, when it comes to cool things, you could print simplified robot models, little team logo trophies, or even team elements that you can give out at events.

Parts I’ve designed and/or printed for this year:

  • Elevator drive chain guard
  • 3 different camera mounts
  • Brace for our intake
  • Climber hook
  • Bushings for our climber arm
  • Spacer for our climber winch
  • Crush blocks for 2x1 extrusion
  • Controller holders for our drive station
  • Fan mounts for our VH-109 home field AP
  • Spacers for our minions
  • Intake sensor mount
  • Swerve module covers
  • End caps for extrusion
  • Ethernet port covers

For prototyping

  • Motor mount pattern guide
  • 1"x1" extrusion bearing blocks

For the shop

  • 0.5" hole spacing cutting guide

We use 3d printing extensively on our robots. Here’s a list of the 3D printed parts on this years:

  • Swerve covers
  • Swerve treads
  • Lifting handles
  • Coral cradle
  • Cage latch for climber
  • Arm pivot with integrated HTD belt sprockets
  • Various HTD sprockets/pulleys for intake and elevator
  • Assorted shaft spacers
  • Frame lowering spacers
  • Box tube crush blocks
  • TPU elevator end-stops/bumpers
  • Bushings for constant force springs
  • Cable combs for wire management
  • Grommets and wire pass-throughs
  • Riser to mount Pigeon under PDH
  • Camera mounts
  • Encoder mount for climb
  • Radio mount/cover
  • RSL mount
  • LaserCAN mounts
  • Anderson plug mount
  • Breaker mount
  • Breaker Cover
